text: Jean de Boishue (born 1943) is a French aristocrat, politician and author. ==Early life== Jean de Boishue was born on September 12, 1943 in Boulogne- Billancourt near Paris.National Assembly: Jean de Boishue ==Career== He joined the Rally for the Republic, a defunct center-right political party. He served as the Mayor of Brétigny-sur-Orge from 1984 to 2001. He served as a member of the National Assembly from March 28, 1993 to April 21, 1997, representing Essonne. ==Bibliography== *Banlieue mon amour (Paris: Éditions de la Table ronde, 1995). *Anti-Secrets (Paris: Editions Plon, 2015). ==References== Category:1943 births Category:Living people Category:People from Boulogne- Billancourt Category:Politicians from Île-de-France Category:Rally for the Republic politicians Category:Deputies of the 10th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic Category:French political writers
